  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>To collect data on ablation procedures in the European pediatric population.</measure>
    <time_frame>After 12 months from the ablation procedure</time_frame>
    <description>Primary outcome will be a combination of efficacy (arrhythmia recurrency) and safety (procedural and late complications)</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>To describe and compare different ablation methodologies</measure>
    <time_frame>After 12 months from the ablation procedure</time_frame>
    <description>Rate of index arrhythmia recurrence and rate of complications will be compared for different ablation technology (electroanatomical mapping system vs standard mapping) and for different energy source(radiofrequency vs cryo)</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
